<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 93 / The Lex Column: Standard Chartered
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
On Monday, Standard Chartered held a meeting for eight selected analysts to
discuss the organisation of its UK operations. On Tuesday and Wednesday, its
share price rose by 6 per cent. Standard emphasises that the analysts'
meeting was of a non-financial nature and the swing in its share price on a
volume of only 3.4m shares reflects the lack of liquidity in its paper. Just
the same, such a sharp movement so soon after such a limited briefing leaves
an uncomfortable feeling. If Standard had something interesting to say about
its UK operations, it could have gone to the small extra trouble of putting
out a statement through the stock exchange.
</TEXT>
