<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 93 / The Lex Column: Tarmac
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Selling holes in the ground is not as profitable as it used to be if
Tarmac's sale of Econowaste is any guide. When Wimpey and NFC sold their
landfill sites, they emerged with stinking profits. Tarmac's Pounds 44m sale
smells far less sweet. This may owe much to the negotiating power of Hanson.
It also reflects the hazards of starting disposal programmes late in the
day. Shareholders may simply be relieved that Tarmac has completed
two-thirds of its targeted Pounds 300m of asset sales. They may prove less
sanguine, though, if Tarmac again trails Wimpey and taps them for more
funds.
