<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 93 / Pollution deal threat to Thorp
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government's decision about whether to give the go-ahead to the Thorp
nuclear reprocessing plant at Sellafield could be complicated by a new
international agreement reached last night.
The Paris Commission Convention on sea pollution, whose 13 signatories
border the north-east Atlantic, voted last night in Berlin to tighten the
rules on discharges of radioactivity to the sea. The UK was the only member
to vote against the proposal.
