   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANIES in London are more optimistic about their prospects for the next
six months than their counterparts in eight other European capitals, a
survey has found, Andrew Taylor writes.
The Confederation of British Industry's London branch conducted the survey
with business organisations in Athens, Berlin, Brussels, Lisbon, Madrid,
Paris, Rome and Valetta.
Companies in London were more optimistic about prospects in every sector
except construction. In banking and finance, London was the only capital
'reporting a more optimistic position compared with six months previously'.
