<TEXT>
MOVENPICK, the Swiss hotel and restaurant chain, yesterday said that Mr
Wolfgang vom Hagen, its former chief executive officer, may have exposed it
to claims of up to SFr5m (Dollars 3.4m).
The directors said they have over a dozen cases involving staff appointments
and dismissals and other alleged violations of company law committed by Mr
vom Hagen that could lead to claims. The statement alleged that Mr vom Hagen
had given orders to external consultants without the knowledge of the
management board, leading to charges of about SFr30,000 per working day in
1992 but no results.
