<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUN 93 / International Company News: Canadian cinema group optimistic
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CINEPLEX ODEON, the Canadian cinema and film distribution group controlled
by the Montreal Bronfman family, expects to return to profit in the third
quarter of this year, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
The group made a first-quarter loss of USDollars 10.8m on revenues of
Dollars 116m, against a loss of Dollars 13.9m on revenues of Dollars 129m a
year earlier.
Debt had been reduced from Dollars 700m to Dollars 385m, cash-flow was
positive and operating expense was under control, Mr Allen Karp, president,
told the AGM. In 1992 Cineplex lost Dollars 41.3m on revenues of Dollars
518m.
Although Cineplex has been heavily restructured, and theatres in several
marginal US markets have been sold, it is still one of North America's
largest cinema operators.
The group has 1,614 screens in 363 locations.
</TEXT>
