FT  16 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Cardiff Property ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CARDIFF Property yesterday announced pre-tax profits up 27 per cent to
Pounds 35,861 for the half year to March 31; it also announced an offer to
acquire the outstanding shares in Village Residential.
Cardiff currently owns 32.8 per cent of Village and a cash offer with part
share alternative is being made to acquire the outstanding equity. Village
is an unquoted residential development company. The assets have been managed
by Cardiff since that date.
The offer values Village at Pounds 970,000. Earnings were 1.19p (1.04p) and
the interim is maintained at 0.85p.
