FT  16 JUN 93 / The Lex Column: BT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SG Warburg's attempts to tighten its grip on BT3 are a quantum change from
past practice on the handling of new issues. If stock exchange members agree
to Warburg's request to move to cash settlement, it will become much harder
to short BT shares. Indeed, it would be interesting to know whether money
brokers have also been asked not to lend stock to those shorting the BT
issue. The rapid flow of information about changes to the BT share register
will also help deter selling. Given that there are so few privatisation
mandates left to win, Warburg's pressure may be unwise. And while shorter
settlement is in principle a good thing, why should the Stock Exchange
single out BT for special treatment?
